{{Quote|Live and let live....unless they get in your way. Then kill them.|Motto of Varna Biqua|<ref name="LFC" />}}
'''Varna Biqua''', like its sister city [[Tolea Biqua]], was a floating city on [[Genarius]] that catered to vice industries, but Varna Biqua focused more on the vice and less on partying. The city sat enshrouded in a perpetual thick cloudbank, rumor saying that crimelord [[Riboga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] had enhanced the clouds to hide something.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Varna Biqua supported a large black market. The trade in illegal substances and weapons were some of the city's biggest industries. For the right price, almost anything could be had in Varna Biqua. The city was a chaotic place, summed up by their motto. When a visitor stepped off their ship, they were on their own, or they can pay for the help of figures such as local "obtainer" [[Quaad Endac]].<ref name="LFC" />

There was some new construction on Varna Biqua in [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]] which drew the attention of the [[Cularin system/Legends|system's]] [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]]. A new docking bay was built which was big enough to hold a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]]&mdash;or [[Thaereian military|Thaereian]]&mdash;cruiser.<ref name="LFC" />

The young thugs known as the [[Blood Velkers]] were commonly causing trouble in this city,<ref name="LFC" /> as was the similar thug gang [[Blood Raptors]].<ref name="POB">{{LivingForce|The Price of Business}}</ref>

